The paper deals with the problem of election manipulation through social influence, which is a topic that falls under the category of social networks and computational social science. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves game theory and approximation algorithms, which suggest that cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are also relevant sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of algorithms for social influence problems, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SOC (Computational Social Science).
